The President made several calls to foreign leaders to discuss the situation in Egypt. He spoke with Prime Minister Erdogan of Turkey, Prime Minister Netanyahu of Israel, King Abdullah of Saudi Arabia, and Prime Minister Cameron of the United Kingdom. The President emphasized his opposition to violence and his support for universal rights, including peaceful assembly and free speech. He also expressed his desire for an orderly transition to a government that reflects the aspirations of the Egyptian people. The President asked for their assessment of the situation and agreed to stay in close contact with them.